English

[edit]
English Wikipedia has an article on:
Partner (surname)
Wikipedia

Proper noun

[edit]

Partner

  1. A surname.

German

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Borrowed from English partner.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): [ˈpaʁtnɐ]
  • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)

Noun

[edit]

Partner m (strong, genitive Partners, plural Partner, feminine Partnerin)

  1. partner, associate (male or of unspecified gender)

Declension

[edit]
Declension of Partner [masculine, strong]
singular plural
indef. def. noun def. noun
nominative ein der Partner die Partner
genitive eines des Partners der Partner
dative einem dem Partner den Partnern
accusative einen den Partner die Partner
